column5: I have a snowmobile , will travel I'm down for whatever I know a few stocked lakes we could hit but nothing spetacular south of north bay.  I'd love to fish in Kearny area as I never have before.   But really whatever works. Anyone down next weekend?    It be cool if a few of us could get together . Let's keep the location to pm's for obvious reasons.
due to lack of interest ..maby a drive to trip?
Would love to go, but anything south of Sundridge/South River is a bit too much of a haul for me for a day trip.
There's a slight chance I could go if it was Haliburton,  Gull would be easy and is decent.  U thinking Saturday?

Would love to go, but anything south of Sundridge/South River is a bit too much of a haul for me for a day trip. ill be coming through your neck of the woods on my way home in june maybe we could meet for a fish then!
I would be down for a day out like that.  A lake with safe ice for sleds would make it even better.  Sled, portable hut and auger, good to go!
Im up for an ofc tour too, just cant make this weekend. I work every other, but keep me in the loop. I know a few spots as well  S.
I know of a very productive, good sized splake lake behind Powassan if anyone would be down to make the trip, bit of a haul for some of you guys I guess.
I think were going to stick a little closer to home for this day trip as were coming from the deep south but later in the season lets do it!
A back lake would be fun but would depend on the weekend.  Joeytier - I'm up that way a fair amount and could possible do the Lake you mentioned, or anything else if I'm not sledding.
